# Commit messages

## Format

```text
<type>: <short summary>

<optional body: context, rationale, notable details>
```

## Types

- **`feat:`** — New behavior users care about
- **`fix:`** — Bug fixes
- **`refactor:`** — Internal change without intended behavior change
- **`chore:`** — Tooling, deps, maintenance

## Rules

### Title

- **One line**, max ~72 characters.
- **Lowercase** description.
- **Present tense** (e.g. `add` not `added`).
- **No trailing period**.
- **Summary**, not a changelog — do not enumerate every file or component.
- **No ticket numbers** in the title if your workflow adds them elsewhere.
- **Do not** put file paths or locations in the title — git shows that.

### Body

- **Optional**, but encouraged when the change has non-obvious context, trade-offs, or touches multiple areas.
- Separated from the title by a **blank line**.
- Wrap at ~100 characters; use **full sentences**.
- Explain the **why** and high-level **what**, not a file-by-file diff.
- Short **bullets** are fine when they genuinely help reviewers or coding agents.
- **Do not** restate the title, do not include AI or tool attribution.

## Examples

### Good (title only)

- `feat: add photo reorder to listing wizard`
- `fix: handle empty upload response`
- `refactor: simplify presigned upload helper`

### Bad

- `Feat: Add feature` (wrong casing)
- `fix: fixed the bug.` (past tense + period)
- `feat: src/studio/foo.tsx` (location in title)

### Verbose title

Bad — crams everything into the title:

- `chore: add CampaignWizardProgressSection and CampaignWizardSuccessSection components, update AGENTS.md with new linting instructions, and refine campaign wizard logic for better code organization`

Good — short title plus body:

```text
feat: add progress and success sections to campaign wizard

Split the campaign wizard into dedicated progress and success sections to improve code
organization and make each step easier to reason about. Also updates AGENTS.md with
linting instructions so agents run the lint step after edits.
```
